CM_ SG_ 146 EnFanReq "This signal is transmitted by powertrain control unit TCM. It stands for the cooling requirement from transmission side. For PWM type cooling fan, it stands for the duty ratio output requirement.";

CM_ SG_ 148 TrCrntShftLvrPosV "Validity of the Trasmission Current Shift Lever PositionˇŁ";
CM_ SG_ 148 TrCrntShftLvrPos "It represents the actual shift level positon. ";
CM_ SG_ 148 TrShftLvrPos "Transmission Shift Lever Position provides an indication of the state of the transmission lever position as selected by the driver. In automatic transmissions, vehicle standards define the order of ranges to be Park, Reverse and Neutral, followed by one or more forward ranges. If powertrain detects that the transmission shift lever system is between states, this signal shall be set to Between Ranges.
In vehicle using Electronic Range Selection (Tap Up/Down Mode Request is set to 'Enable Electronic Range Select') this signal will reflect the forward range selected by the driver by ERS switches.
The IPK shall use this signal for displaying the range selected.";
CM_ SG_ 148 TrShftLvrPosV "If any diagnostics determine that the sensor information used to create Transmission Shift Lever Position is unreliable and a corresponding emissions related DTC has been set, this signal shall be set to Invalid.";

CM_ SG_ 152 PTBrkPdlPos "This signal is received by powertrain control unit TCM. It is used by creep control function and neutral idle control function.";
CM_ SG_ 152 EnSpd "This signal is transmitted by powertrain control unit ECM. It represents the unfiltered, high resolution engine speed in revolutions per minute, determined from the engine sensors available.";
CM_ SG_ 152 AccelEfctvPos "This signal is transmitted by the ECM. It represents
the larger of the driver request via the accelerator
pedal (pedal position, mode switches and other
parameters as well as filtering) and vehicle speed
control request. When cruise control is active, this
signal is calculated based on cruise torque requirement. When cruise control is not active, this signal equals to ˇ°Accelerator Actual Positionˇ±.If ˇ°Accelerator Actual Position Validityˇ± is ˇ°Invalidˇ±,
ˇ°Accelerator Effective Positionˇ± should always be ˇ°0ˇ±";
CM_ SG_ 152 AccelActuPos "Accelerator Actual Positionˇ± will not be used by ECM to honor driver's torque request, but will be used to control the throttle position in KL15 state.Throttle position should have linear relationship with accelerator pedal position.When the validity flag is received as ˇ°Invalidˇ±, ECM should consider ˇ°Accelerator Actual Postionˇ±as 0. ";
CM_ SG_ 152 AccelActuPosV "When either one sensor input failure or two sensor
inputs are not coherent, ˇ°Electric Powertrain
Accelerator Actual Position Validityˇ± will be set to 'Invalid'. ˇ°Electric Powertrain Accelerator Actual Positionˇ± should always be 0 in this situation. ";
CM_ SG_ 152 AccelEfctvPosV "Accelerator Effective Position Validty( to ADAS)";
CM_ SG_ 152 PTBrkPdlDscrtInptSts "Powertrain Brake Pedal Discrete Input Status
The ECM shall report the state of the hardwire brake switch input through this signal. This signal only indicates whether the brake pedal has been applied, and it is not necessarily indicative of the state of the stop lamps.";
CM_ SG_ 152 PTBrkPdlDscrtInptStsV "If ECM detects the incoherency error of the brake switches input, the validity flag should be set to
ˇ°Invalidˇ±. At the same time, ˇ°Electric Powertrain Brake
Pedal Discrete Input Statusˇ± should be set to ˇ°Brake
Appliedˇ±.";
CM_ SG_ 152 EnSpdSts "This signal is transmitted by powertrain control unit ECM. It should be used together with Engine Speed.
Degraded Operation:
This signal should be set to ˇ°Degraded Operationˇ± if a
diagnostic code is set for the primary sensor providing
the data and a backup value is being calculated from
other than the primary sensor. Primary sensor is used to be crankshaft position sensor and backup sensor is used to be camshaft position sensor.
Normal Operation:
It will be set to ˇ°Normal Operationˇ± when the ECM has not determined that there are diagnostic faults of the engine speed sensor or engine speed system.
Invalid:
It should be set to ˇ°Invalidˇ± if the diagnostic code is set
for the primary sensor, and no backup value is available or backup sensor is also failure.";

